<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Greek Museum Opens  </HEADLINE>
By THEODORA TONGAS
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- Greece has a lot of history. And a lot of
museums.
</P>
<P>
   Now one museum is offering visitors a glimpse of it all, packing
exhibits that span more than 5,000 years into one place.
</P>
<P>
   The Benaki Museum in Athens reopened its doors Friday after a
renovation that cost $20 million and took more than a decade.
</P>
<P>
   ''We wanted to offer a summary but (also) panoramic view of
Greek history,'' said museum director Angelos Delivorias. ''It is
the only museum that unifies Greek time and space under one roof.''
</P>
<P>
   Delivorias led an army of restoration workers and other experts
who arranged more than 20,000 items chronologically in 36 rooms in
a radical restoration that now uses an area more than double the
original 32,300 square feet.
</P>
<P>
   Collections were enriched. A wing was added, display cases were
installed and everything behind the building's neoclassical
exterior was modernized.
</P>
<P>
   At one end of the collection are rare hammered gold cups from
the Aegean of the early Bronze Age. At the other, the two Nobel
Prizes for literature won by George Seferis in 1963 and Odysseus
Elytis in 1979.
</P>
<P>
   In between are early Christian Fayum death portraits, Byzantine
icons and scores of local costumes from around Greece. There's a
copy of the first Greek Constitution signed in 1844, and weapons
used by the poet Lord Byron in Greece's war of independence.
</P>
<P>
   Delivorias said the exhibits on display include just 20 percent
of the museum's collection. Room for Greek items is so limited that
Islamic and Chinese works once on display will be moved to other
sites.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-10-00 0018 </TRAILER>
