<HEADLINE> Athletics 3, Dodgers 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Olmedo Saenz hit a tiebreaking two-run homer
in the eighth inning Friday night, and the Oakland Athletics beat
the Los Angeles Dodgers 3-1 for their sixth victory in seven
interleague games.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Giambi drew a two-out walk off Antonio Osuna (0-3) before
Saenz lined his fifth homer into the left-field pavilion.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Tam (1-2) bailed Tim Hudson out of a seventh-inning jam and
went on to pitch 1 2-3 scoreless innings, allowing one hit and
striking out four. Jason Isringhausen pitched a perfect ninth for
his 15th save in 18 chances.
</P>
<P>
   The A's, held to one hit through 5 2-3 innings by Carlos Perez,
tied it in the sixth when Giambi walked with two outs, Saenz
singled and Ben Grieve doubled into the right-field corner.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Grudzielanek's first-inning homer had given the Dodgers a
1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Perez held Oakland hitless until Miguel Tejada doubled sharply
into the left-field corner with two outs in the fifth. Before that,
Oakland's only runners had been Saenz -- who reached in both the
second and fourth innings on errors by third baseman Kevin Elster --
and Rudy Christensen, who walked leading off the game, then was
throw out attempting to steal second.
</P>
<P>
   In his sharpest outing of the season, Perez allowed one run
three hits in seven innings, lowering his ERA to 4.71.
</P>
<P>
   Hudson struck out eight in 6 1-3 innings, giving up one run,
four hits and four walks.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Dodgers have signed 11 of their draft selections, the
highest among them 7th-round pick C Jared Price. Others include Ps
Shane Nance, Jonathan Lorenzen, Jason Olson, Casey Kennedy, Steve
Langone and Clifton Glidewell; OFs Ronte Langs and Nicholas
Alvarez; and INFs Adrian Mendoza and Zachary Leske. ... The
Dodgers' Orel Hershiser went four-plus innings Friday night in the
latest start of his self-imposed exile to Single-A San Bernardino,
allowing three runs and six hits against Mudville. Hershiser, who
made 76 pitches, is on standby if Perez is yanked from the
rotation. ... Grieve had been 2-for-23 in interleague play until
his game-tying double. ... Matt Stairs was 0-for-3 off Perez and is
6-for-55 against left-handers this season, the worst mark in the AL
</P>
</TEXT>
