<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 08:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Long Island telemarketer alerted police of Mamaroneck attack  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - When an alleged rapist entered the Mamaroneck
lingerie shop where his ex-girlfriend works, she was on the phone
with a telemarketer on Long Island who notified police.
</P>
<P>
   Meryl Greene called Nassau police after hearing William Milligan
threaten the woman Thursday afternoon, Newsday reported Saturday.
She was referred to the New Rochelle police, who in turn alerted
police in Mamaroneck. As a result, authorities arrived on scene
before Milligan could escape.
</P>
<P>
   Armed with a rifle, Milligan, 56, of Gardiner, held off police
for half an hour and then was coaxed into surrendering as
sharpshooters lined the village's main street and perched on
rooftops above.
</P>
<P>
   Milligan was ordered to the psychiatric unit of the Westchester
County Jail after his arraignment Thursday night on a rape charge.
</P>
<P>
   Milligan had walked into Sheer Perfection on Mamaroneck Avenue,
where his former girlfriend works, at 12:19 p.m. Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Milligan released the 49-year-old woman, who was taken to an
ambulance with a bandage on her knee. But he stayed in the shop as
police blocked off streets and ordered merchants to lock their
doors.
</P>
<P>
   Detective Sgt. Robert Holland of the Mamaroneck police reached
Milligan by phone and told him, ''this wasn't worth dying for,''
Holland said afterward.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's over an ex-girlfriend and they had some problems,''
Holland said. ''I told him they might be able to work it out. He
was really bent on suicide.'' Milligan emerged, dropped to one knee
and surrendered.
</P>
<P>
   If convicted of first-degree rape, Milligan could be sentenced
to up to 25 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
   The victim had ordered a catalog from American Royal Arts in
Westbury, where Greene works. Armed with the victim's home address,
Mamaroneck police found the woman's daughter, who directed them to
the lingerie store.
</P>
</TEXT>
