<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Water levels lower than average in most of the Great Lakes  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	
<TEXT>
<P>
   At the end of June, water levels on all the Great Lakes except Lake
Ontario were significantly below the 80-year June average, causing
problems for lake shipping. Here is where each lake stands compared
with the average:
</P>
<P>
   -Lake Superior, 11 inches below average.
</P>
<P>
   -Lake Huron, 22 inches below average.
</P>
<P>
   -Lake Michigan, 22 inches below average.
</P>
<P>
   -Lake Ontario, 6 inches above average and 22 inches below the
highest June level set in 1952.
</P>
<P>
   -Lake Erie, 7 inches below average and 35 inches below the
highest June average, set in 1986.
</P>
<P>
   Source: U.S. Army Corps of Engineers.
</P>
</TEXT>
