<HEADLINE> 21 horses dead in fire at Brooklyn stable  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Twenty-one mostly privately owned horses died in
a fire that engulfed a Brooklyn stable, but three other animals
were rescued unharmed early Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The blaze in the single-story Bergan Beach Stables in the Mill
Basin neighborhood started at about 11:45 p.m. Friday, fire
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators were at the scene Saturday, trying to determine
the cause of the blaze, which left many of the horses fatally
burned.
</P>
<P>
   ''Some of the horses were very badly burned,'' said James
Spollen, a fire department spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 21 that died, two were owned by the New York City Parks
Department.
</P>
<P>
   Three horses survived; two were taken to an NYPD horse facility,
and the third was transported by its owner.
</P>
<P>
   The flames, which totally destroyed the stable, were under
control by 1 a.m.
</P>
</TEXT>
