<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 18:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ga. Newswoman Shot And Killed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOULTRIE, Ga. (AP) -- A newswoman with The Moultrie Observer was
killed while sitting in her car, and hours later her estranged
husband died of a gunshot wound that police said may have been
self-inflicted.
</P>
<P>
   Kim Zeigler Nunez, 39, was shot once in the head with a 9 mm
pistol Friday night at a traffic light, police said.
</P>
<P>
   She apparently was driving back to the newspaper office to work
on Sunday's edition after taking her son to a skating rink,
Observer managing editor Dwain Walden said.
</P>
<P>
   Her estranged husband, Raul Nunez, was later found wounded in
his pickup in nearby Funston and died on the way to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   A 9 mm pistol and a spent shell casing were found with him, and
police said he may have shot himself. Raul Nunez had been charged a
week earlier with making terroristic threats against his wife.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-10-00 1817 </TRAILER>
