<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marijuana Found at Royal Palace  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Police raided the kitchen of Buckingham Palace and
found a small amount of marijuana, Scotland Yard said Saturday. No
arrests were made.
</P>
<P>
   ''A very small quantity of a cannabis plant was discovered and
has been taken away by police for examination,'' a Yard spokesman
said on condition of anonymity. The amount involved was minute, he
said, and it was uncertain if further action would be taken.
</P>
<P>
   The tabloid News of the World reported Sunday that a member of
the palace staff had tipped off the police Royalty Protection
Squad, and that the marijuana was found Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
   Buckingham Palace gave no comment, saying it was a police
matter.
</P>
</TEXT>
