<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 20:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WPIX, WPTZ win most TV awards; WSLU, WBFO capture most radio honors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) - New York City's WPIX and WPTZ in
Plattsburgh dominated the television competition in the 1999 New
York State Associated Press Broadcasters awards Saturday night,
while WBFO in Buffalo and WSLU in Canton captured the most honors
in the radio category.
</P>
<P>
   WPIX won four first-place awards in the competition for stations
in the state's largest TV market, including top honors in the
sports category for its coverage of the death of former New York
Yankee great Joe DiMaggio.
</P>
<P>
   WABC-TV in New York City won top honors in three categories, as
did News 12 on Long Island.
</P>
<P>
   WPTZ took home five first-place awards in the small-market
competition, while in the contest for medium-sized markets, three
stations won two awards apiece: WGRZ in Buffalo, R News in
Rochester and WTVH in Syracuse.
</P>
<P>
   Binghamton's WBNG won top honors in two categories. Other
first-place winners were WOKR in Rochester, WIXT in Syracuse, the
Albany area's WRGB, WWNY in Watertown, and WUTR and WKTV, both in
Utica.
</P>
<P>
   In the radio competition, WSLU came away with four first-place
awards in the small-market category. WFAS in White Plains, WRVO in
Oswego and Long Island's WSUF each won two first-place awards.
</P>
<P>
   Among stations in the medium-sized radio market, WBFO garnered
three first-place awards. Rochester's WHAM, WGY in Albany and WSYR
in Syracuse each won two, while Albany's WAMC captured one
first-place honor.
</P>
<P>
   In the large-market competition WINS, WNYC, WCBS and WOR won two
first-place awards apiece, while WBBR captured one.
</P>
<P>
   The awards competition was for the 1999 calendar year and was
open to the more than 150 radio and television stations in New York
state that are AP members.
</P>
<P>
   The honors were given out Saturday night at the NYSAPBA's annual
awards banquet held at a Saratoga Springs hotel.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
