<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lions To Sign QB Stoney Case  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Lions have agreed to sign
quarterback Stoney Case.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have agreed to terms with him on a contract,'' Lions
spokesman Steve Reaven said. ''The intent is to have him on the
field by Tuesday'' for the final week of the Lions' voluntary
summer workouts.
</P>
<P>
   Case, 27, was expected to sign Monday, Reaven said. He would not
disclose contract terms.
</P>
<P>
   According to an item on ESPN's Web site, the former Baltimore
Ravens quarterback would agree to a one-year contract worth
$465,000, including a $25,000 signing bonus.
</P>
<P>
   A message left Saturday with Case's agent, Gary Wichard, was not
immediately returned.
</P>
<P>
   Starter Charlie Batch suffered a leg injury Monday that will
keep him sidelined for three months.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Bobby Ross has said he wanted another quarterback signed
by Tuesday to share the workload with Mike Tomczak and Steve
Stenstrom during the last three voluntary workouts and in training
camp, the Detroit Free Press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The Lions contacted former Detroit quarterback Rodney Peete and
his agent after Batch's injury, but did not make him a formal
offer, Reaven said.
</P>
</TEXT>
