<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberty 70, Fever 62  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Crystal Robinson scored five of her 19
points during a second-half burst that carried the New York Liberty
to a 70-62 WNBA win over the Indiana Fever on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   New York extended a one-point lead into an 11-point cushion by
outscoring Indiana 13-3 over a 6:13 stretch of the second half.
Robinson's 3-pointer from the right side gave the Liberty a 66-55
lead with 1:35 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Becky Hammon scored 16 points, Tari Phillips 15 and Vickie
Johnson 12 for New York (3-4). The Liberty, who hit 12 of their
first 15 shots in the second half, finished at 54 percent
(27-for-50) for the game.
</P>
<P>
   Stephanie McCarty led Indiana (2-3) with 15 points and eight
assists. Kara Wolters, the Fever's 6-foot-7 center, added 13 points
and nine rebounds. Indiana shot 26-for-66 (39 percent) from the
field.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson scored 14 points as the teams spent the first half
trading scoring runs, with New York leading 31-30 at intermission.
Robinson shot 8-for-12 for the game, including 3-for-5 from 3-point
range.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
