<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 22:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lynx 66, Sol 55  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Katie Smith scored 28 points to lead the Minnesota
Lynx to a 66-55 victory over the Miami Sol on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota (4-2) won its third straight, despite the absence of
starting center Kristin Folkl for most of the game. Folkl banged
heads with teammate Marla Brumfield three minutes in and didn't
return.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, the WNBA's leading scorer, made 14-of-16 free throws,
including eight straight in the final eight minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Betty Lennox scored nine of her 12 points in the first half, and
Grace Daley added eight for Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Reserve Sheri Sam scored 15, and Katrina Colleton and Jameka
Jones added 10 each for the Sol (1-4), who are still looking for
their first franchise victory at home after three losses at the
AmericanAirlines Arena.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota hit six straight free throws, with Smith converting
four, to boost its lead to 56-39 with 4:14 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Sam scored nine straight points, including a 3-pointer, but
Smith countered with a 3-pointer to boost Minnesota's lead to 59-48
with 2:17 left.
</P>
<P>
   Jones' runner in the lane made it 60-51, but Smith made four
straight free throws to secure the victory.
</P>
<P>
   Lennox scored nine points in the first half and Smith added
eight, including a 3-pointer with 50 seconds left to help the Lynx
take a 30-17 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   Former Georgia Tech standout Kisha Ford, signed on Friday,
scored the first seven points of an 11-1 Sol spurt to cut the
deficit to 45-36 with 8:03 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams shot under 37 percent from the field for the game,
but the Lynx went 22-for-29 from the free-throw line, to Miami's
13-for-22.
</P>
<P>
   Daley hit two driving layups, and Smith added a 3-pointer and
two free throws to cap an 11-0 run, giving the Lynx a 19-11 lead
they wouldn't relinquish. Miami was scoreless for 6:38 during the
spurt.
</P>
</TEXT>
